pus":1890,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"هَلَّ","root":"","pos":"P","occurrence_count":93},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["particle"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n44322"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%91"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"particle","gloss":"introduces a positive yes-no question","examples":[{"text":"هَلْ فَتَحْتَ النَّافِذَةَ؟","english":"Did you open the window?"},{"text":"هَلِ ٱلْوَلَدُ فِي ٱلْمَدْرَسَةِ؟","english":"Is the boy at school?"}]},{"pos":"particle","gloss":"indicates a suggestion","examples":[{"text":"هَلْ أَدُلُّكُمْ عَلَى تِجَارَةٍ تُنْجِيكُم مِنْ عَذَابٍ أَلِيمٍ","english":"Shall I guide you to a transaction that will save you from a painful punishment?"}]},{"pos":"particle","gloss":"indicates an exclusive disjunction with أَمْ (ʔam, “or”), as in alternative questions","examples":[{"text":"فَإِذَا أَرَادَ الْمُرِيدُ أَنَّ عُقُولَ الْعُقَلَاءِ لَمْ تَصِلْ إلَى مَعْرِفَةِ مِثْلِ هَذِهِ الْأُمُورِ فَهَذَا صَحِيحٌ وَأَمَّا إذَا أَرَادَ أَنَّ الْعُقَلَاءَ لَيْسَ عِنْدَهُمْ عِلْمٌ وَلَا يَقِينٌ بَلْ حَيْرَةٌ وَرَيْبٌ فَهَذَا بَاطِلٌ قَطْعًا. وَمَا ذُكِرَ عَنْ ذِي النُّونِ \" فِي هَذَا الْبَابِ مَعَ أَنَّ ذَا النُّونِ قَدْ وَقَعَ مِنْهُ كَلَامٌ أَنْكَرَ عَلَيْهِ وَعَزَّرَهُ الْحَارِثُ بْنُ مِسْكِينٍ وَطَلَبَهُ الْمُتَوَكِّلُ إلَى بَغْدَادَ وَاتُّهِمَ بِالزَّنْدَقَةِ وَجَعَلَهُ النَّاسُ مَنْ الْفَلَاسِفَةِ فَمَا أَدْرِي هَلْ قَالَ هَذَا أَمْ لَا؟","english":"If it is meant that the minds of right-minded men have not attained knowledge of such things, then yes, this is true. If, however, it is meant that not even right-minded men have knowledge of nor are certain about anything but are rather in doubt and perplexity, this is absolutely false, together with what Ḏū al-Nūn said on this matter. Ḏū al-Nūn himself, though, did say things for which he was reproached and chastised by al-Ḥāriṯ ibn Miskīn, and he was sent for by al-Mutawakkil and was charged with heresy and has been deemed to be among the Philosophers, and so I do not know whether he said this or not."}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Univerbation of هَـ (ha-, now interrogative أَ (ʔa)) + لـ (l-, affirmative particle, found as لَـ (la-, “truly”) and the exhortative لِـ (li-) the vowel of which disappears between فَـ (fa-) or وَ (wa) and a following verb)."},"ipa":["/hal/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n44322","headword_ar":"هَلْ","root":"hl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"may be originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halow","text_ar":"هَلْو"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haloY","text_ar":"هَلْى"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hal~","text_ar":"هَلّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Akh, in S, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bl","text_ar":"بل"},{"kind":"text","text":":) see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balo","text_ar":"بَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"halo","text_ar":"هَلْ"},{"kind":"text","text":"followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY","text_ar":"اـِلَى"},{"kind":"text","text":": see the latter. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaY~ hala","text_ar":"حَىّ هَلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HY","text_ar":"حى"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hal~aA","text_ar":"هَلَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaD~apN","text_ar":"حَضَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano","text_ar":"عَنْ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter part, and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawolaA","text_ar":"لَوْلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^al~aA","text_ar":"اَلَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]}]}}